  "texts": [
    "For example, Li et al. (2010) used an automatic micro-optical sectioning tomography (MOST) to obtain a mesoscale atlas of the mouse brain.",
    "This strategy integrates a microtome, light microscope, and image recorder, and allows for simultaneous imaging and sectioning (Li et al., 2010).",
    "Another possible approach was the use of post-mortem axonal projections enhanced by green fluorescent protein (EGFP)-labeling (Oh et al., 2014).",
    "They imaged many small patches of brain tissue with two-photon microscopy to form a big image with cellular-level resolution (Oh et al., 2014).",
    "Imaging at this scale in larger FOV took 18.5 h of scanning and resulted in a 750 GB raw dataset."
